    <item>
      <title>Hyperscanning</title>
      <link>/project/hyperscanning/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2015 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/project/hyperscanning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Short Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During a conversation, speakers tend to converge towards each other. This phenomenon is called speech convergence. Aim of this project is to find what happens in the participants brain during speech convergence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The steps are -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quantifying speech convergence and mark the time points in the conversation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using the markers we group the corresponding brain recordings and find some neural markers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
